cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.DL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of answering conjunctive queries over a set of facts extended with existential rules, which is a prominent problem in knowledge representation and databases. This makes cs.AI and cs.DB the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the application of these concepts to query answering in ontologies, which makes cs.LO and cs.DL likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of query answering for acyclic ontologies, which makes cs.CR a possible category.
